# Gene Expression Visualiser

A Python tool for gene expression analysis and visualisation.
Takes a raw counts matrix, performs CPM normalisation, log2 transformation,
simple differential expression analysis, and generates 4 publication-ready figures.

---

## Features

- CPM normalisation + log2 transformation
- Per-gene differential expression (Welch's t-test, log2FC)
- Top N variable gene heatmap (hierarchically clustered, z-scored)
- Volcano plot with significant gene labels
- Sample-sample Pearson correlation heatmap
- PCA plot coloured by experimental group
- DE results exported as CSV
- No sklearn or R required — pure Python + numpy + scipy

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/gene-expression-visualiser.git
cd gene-expression-visualiser
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**Requirements:**
```
numpy
pandas
matplotlib
scipy
```

---

## Input format

CSV file — genes as rows, samples as columns:

```
gene_id,ctrl_1,ctrl_2,ctrl_3,treat_1,treat_2,treat_3
GENE_0001,120,135,118,450,480,465
GENE_0002,80,90,85,85,92,88
GENE_0003,500,520,490,100,95,110
```

---

## Usage

```bash
# Basic
python expression_visualiser.py \
    -i counts.csv \
    -o figures/ \
    --group1 ctrl_1,ctrl_2,ctrl_3 \
    --group2 treat_1,treat_2,treat_3

# With custom labels and more heatmap genes
python expression_visualiser.py \
    -i counts.csv \
    -o figures/ \
    --group1 ctrl_1,ctrl_2,ctrl_3 \
    --group2 treat_1,treat_2,treat_3 \
    --group1-name "Vehicle" \
    --group2-name "Drug treated" \
    --top-genes 75
```

