## Output files

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `*_heatmap.png` | Top variable genes, hierarchically clustered, z-scored |
| `*_volcano.png` | log2FC vs -log10(p), significant genes labelled |
| `*_correlation.png` | Sample Pearson correlation matrix |
| `*_pca.png` | PCA coloured by group |
| `*_de_results.csv` | Full DE table: log2FC, p-value, significance |

---

## Differential expression criteria

| Criterion | Threshold |
|-----------|-----------|
| Fold change | \|log2FC\| > 1 (i.e. >2x change) |
| Significance | p < 0.05 (Welch's t-test) |

> **Note:** This tool uses a simple t-test approximation. For rigorous DE analysis
> use DESeq2 or edgeR in R, which apply negative binomial models and
> proper multiple testing correction (Benjamini-Hochberg FDR).

